    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In his review of ''Johnny Cash: The Biography'' (Oct. 15), Douglas Brinkley observes: ''You can't walk into a Starbucks and not hear him singing Gordon Lightfoot's 'If You Could Read My Mind' or Ian Tyson's 'Four Strong Winds.' The redemptive sprit of Johnny Cash -- the American spirit -- is very much alive.'' Redemptive maybe, but not American. Gordon Lightfoot? Ian Tyson? Both Canadian, eh.</p>
        <p>Renton Stevenson</p>
        <p>Toronto</p>
      </block>
